DUNGEON CRAWLER - ASSIGNMENT_NUM

SUMMARY:
This roguelike dungeon game in now implemented with a playable character. Navigate with vim-like
keybindings. Players are now able to utilize features like the Monster Menu, and the use of stairs
to evaid enemies.

DUNGEON CRAWLER
    --save   : Save a randomly generated dungeon to binary file in ~/.rlg327/dungeon. This file
                will be created if does not already exist.
    --load   : Load a saved dungeon from disk.
    --nummon : Tell the game how many monsters to load at the start. Choose a number between
                1-15. Monster locations are not persistent.
BUILD & EXECUTION
    To build this project, simpily run make in the project's root directory. This when create
    a executable binary named dungeon_crawler. All build files are kept in /build, and other
    binaries are kept in /bin.

KNOWN ISSUES
    1. Monster characteristics are not fully implemented. Sixteen character combinations will 
        be available for the v1.06 release. All monsters are Telepathic and Intelligent, but half
        have the ability to Tunnel and the other half do not.

